<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Emulation begginer, where to start]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4231&amp;p=35044#p35044"><![CDATA[
I'd say start by emulating the CPU and memory access. Then write some simple test sequences in hardcoded 6502 machine code and have your CPU emulator run them and check that the result is what you'd expect (you can output the CPU's status to a text console or whatever).<br />Then fix your memory access routines to handle the basic memory layout of the NES and try to run some really basic demo ROM, like ColourBars.<br />After that you can start adding some graphical output, joypad input etc.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1181">mic_</a> — Fri Jul 18, 2008 9:57 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
